# Live MCP runtime authority

This project can be ahead of the connected KAIROS MCP runtime.

- Read the MCP version shown at connect when that information is available.
- Treat the connected server's tool names, schemas, and tool descriptions as the authority for real MCP calls.
- Treat this worktree's source, tests, and embedded docs as the authority for implementation work in this branch.
- If the runtime contract and the worktree contract differ, state that mismatch before proceeding.
- Do not use the current branch name by itself as protocol authority.
